  "elapsed_s": 8.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "He saw us through the window, and I saw him.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And then the train moved on, and we lost each other in a sea of people but eventually hooked up with him again.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And of course there was a joyous reunion.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "My mother had not packed a lot, because we didn't know we were leaving for good.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "We were leaving for an interim.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "My mother said to me later that maybe she would have never left if she thought that she was leaving my grandmother-- her mother-- and my aunt and my other grandmother forever.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "This was not the parting it was, that night we left.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "It was for interim.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "It was for a day or two, a week, a month.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Nothing serious.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Didn't turn out that way, of course.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "But we arrived in Bialystok, and my father had rented a one-room flat overlooking [?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Strashun ?] Street.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "That was the Jewish quarter in Vilna.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And it was the butchers' street.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "It was the street on which all the butcher shops of the world, I thought, existed, where you could, you could buy anything that related to a, to a cow or an oxen or to a chicken or to a geese-- a goose or what have you.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And the, the street was laden with meats of every kind, butcher shops of every kind.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "In fact, the, the gutter, often as not, was red from blood of the, of the killing of the animals involved and the, the wielding of the butcher knives and so forth as they cut off, for their customers that came to, to buy meat, slices of beef or slices of turkeys or goose.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And the, the, the people would come to buy.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "They'd come with their [NON-ENGLISH], the, the handbags and the bags.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
